<figureCitation id="69BC2A7DFF9DFFECFEE1FE6CC4D7EA88" box="[335,406,385,411]" captionStart="Figures 10–16" captionStartId="8.[192,279,1799,1825]" captionTargetBox="[216,1416,213,1768]" captionTargetId="figure-18@8.[216,1416,213,1768]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 10–16. Dyslexia belamyi Skelley and Gasca-Álvarez, holotype male, unless stated otherwise. 10) Dorsal habitus.11) Ventral habitus. 12) Lateral habitus. 13) Anterior dorsal oblique view of head and pronotum. 14) Anterior ventral oblique view of head and pronotum, not male protibial dimorphism. 15) Male genitalia. 16) Female genitalia, allotype." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5353888" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5353888/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="6">10–16</figureCitation>
